                    </h2>
                    <p class="text-lg text-[#5A5A5A] leading-relaxed mt-2">
                        Under the mission, individuals are suggested to create health IDs to standardize the process of identification across healthcare providers. To issue UHID (Universal Health ID), the system collects certain basic details of the individual, including demographic, location, family/relationship, and contact details. The Health ID will uniquely identify individuals, authenticating them, and sharing their health records (only with informed consent) with multiple healthcare systems and various stakeholders.
