                        Health Records (PHR)
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-[#5A5A5A] leading-relaxed">
                        PHR is an electronic form of medical record(s) of an individual which conforms to nationally recognized interoperability standards. It is managed, shared, and controlled by the individual, and can be drawn from multiple sources. The most notable feature of the PHR: The information is under the control of the individual.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-[#5A5A5A] leading-relaxed">
                        The Personal Health Record-System (PHR) will enable individuals to manage complete information about his/her healthcare. The information would include the longitudinal record, comprising of his/her health data, lab reports, discharge summaries, treatment details, across one or multiple health facilities.
