            <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-[26px] font-semibold text-[#004A86]">
                Digital Health Incentive Scheme
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
                Since the launch of Ayushman Bharat Digital Mission (ABDM), digital health records have grown significantly. However, many people are still using non-digital healthcare services, so there's still room to grow and completely digitize health across India.
                In an effort to boost digital health transactions, the National Health Authority (NHA) has launched an incentive scheme called Digital Health Incentive Scheme (DHIS) for all healthcare providers contributing to the digital health ecosystem.
                Through DHIS, doctors can play an instrumental role in the digitization of patient health records while earning up to ₹4 crores.
                <br /><br />
                The Digital Health Incentive Scheme also encourages makers of digital health software, like Hospital/Health Management Information Systems (HMIS) and Laboratory Management Information Systems (LMIS), to offer their software at a fair and affordable price.
            </p>
